citations:
    citation-agot-catelyn-vii:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Catelyn VII"
            text_from_source: "When she was done, her uncle remained silent for a long time, as his horse negotiated the steep, rocky trail."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Catelyn, Tyrion, Bronn, Marillion, and Brynden Tully travel through the Vale to the Eyrie. Brynden warns Catelyn that Lysa has changed. Lord Nestor Royce greets them at the Gates of the Moon. Mya Stone (Robert's bastard daughter) guides Catelyn by night up through waycastles Stone, Snow, and Sky to the Eyrie. Catelyn meets Lysa Arryn and the sickly young Robert Arryn, Lord of the Eyrie. Lysa reveals Jon Arryn's last words: 'The seed is strong.'"
